PART 1Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äì Graph Coloring
üîπ What is Graph Coloring?

Graph coloring means assigning colors to vertices such that:

No two adjacent vertices have the same color.

üìå This is called Proper Vertex Coloring.

üîπ Chromatic Number (œá(G)) ‚Äî VERY IMPORTANT

The minimum number of colors required to properly color a graph is called the chromatic number.

Examples:

Complete graph 
