PART 2Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äì Planar Graphs
üîπ What is a Planar Graph?

A graph is planar if it can be drawn on a plane without edge crossings.

üìå Important:
Edges may cross in drawing but if can be rearranged to avoid crossing ‚Üí planar.

üîπ Euler‚Äôs Formula (EXTREMELY IMPORTANT)

